          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-copy-7-1682418553072-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve the <strong>chopped creamed coconut </strong>and <strong>tamari soy sauce </strong>in 350ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[525ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml]</span> <strong>boiled water </strong>– this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Bash your <strong>lemongrass</strong> with a <strong>rolling</strong> <strong>pin </strong>and cut in half</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-copy-7-1682418559987-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
