          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-copy-6-1682418564835-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the veg has softened, add your <strong>red Thai curry paste</strong> to the pot with the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and<strong> ginger</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>coconut stock </strong>with the <strong>halved</strong> <strong>lemongrass </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium-low and cook for 5-6 min or until thickened</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-6-1682418569745-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-copy-6-1682418569745-x400.jpg",
